Some leaders of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) have mounted pressure on the Speaker Emmanuel Tonye Isenah to resign his position. They were said to have insisted that Isenah must give his position to a lawmaker from Southern Ijaw Local Government Area to enable the PDP secure the council’s vote. The plot to get Isenah out his position has, however, introduced fresh crisis into the PDP, which is still trying to recover from post primary election controversies. Details shortly…